Study on Freight OD Spatial Distribution Relations Based on the Input-Output Model

CHEN Li-qin1 YONG Qi-ming2 LIANG Yi2 XUE Mei-hua3
1． Wenzhou Expressway Engineering Construction Headquarters Wenzhou 325000 China 2． Regional Planning and Transportation System Institute University of Shanghai for Science ＆ Technology Shanghai 200093 China
3． Central and Southern China Municipal Engineering Design ＆ Research Institute Shanghai 200093 China

Abstract This paper summarizes the development rules of regional freight． According to the spatial OD distribution of freight demand and its relevant degree with various social economy evaluation indexes their relational model is established to estimate freight volume and OD spatial distribution relations． Key words OD spatial distribution input and output arterial highway freight distribution

